text: This is a list of prime ministers of Togo since the creation of the job of Prime Minister in 1960, to the present day."Togo Leader Adds to Cabinet to End Crisis", The New York Times, 2 January 1992. A total of twelve people have been Prime Minister of Togo. ==Key== ;Political parties * * * * * * * ;Other factions * ==Key== Portrait Name Term of office Political party Took office Left office 1 Nicolas Grunitzky 1956 1960 MPT 2 Sylvanus Olympio 1960 1963 CUT 3 Emmanuel Bodjollé 1963 1963 Military (1) Nicolas Grunitzky 1963 1967 MPT 4 Kléber Dadjo 1967 1967 Military 5 Gnassingbé Eyadéma 1967 1991 Military / RPT 6 Joseph Kokou Koffigoh 1991 1994 CFN 7 Edem Kodjo 1994 1996 UDT 8 Kwassi Klutse 1996 1999 RPT 9 Eugene Koffi Adoboli 1999 2000 RPT 10 Agbéyomé Kodjo 2000 2002 RPT 11 Koffi Sama 2002 2005 RPT 7 Edem Kodjo 9 June 2005 2006 UDT 12 Yawovi Agboyibo 2006 2007 CAR 13 Komlan Mally 2007 2008 RPT 14 Gilbert Houngbo 2008 2012 Independent 15 Kwesi Ahoomey-Zunu 2012 2015 CPP / UNIR 16 Komi Sélom Klassou 2015 2020 UNIR 17 Victoire Tomegah Dogbé 2020 Incumbent UNIR ==References== ==Other websites== *World Statesmen – Togo *1992 Constitution of Togo (as amended in 2007) *
